parameters: It's not good to just barge in like that...
It's not good to just barge in like that...
It's not good to just barge in like that...

Doctor: Your son's condition remains unchanged. We
are doing everything we can, so please rest
assured.

Doctor: This is the second one this month... We
need to improve the treatment of the nurses
soon...

It seems like you're troubled about something...
Should I talk to you?

Doctor: Oh, Nagatsuki-san. I apologize, it was
just a soliloquy so please don't mind.

Doctor: More importantly, it seems like your son's
condition is improving, which is truly a relief.

Doctor: Embarrassingly enough, we haven't been
able to clearly determine why there has been a
sudden improvement...

It's thanks to the hard work of all the doctors
and nurses.

I should thank Nurse Yamazaki later, since I've
been well taken care of by her...
Doctor: Yamazaki... resigned the other day.

Huh... Could it be that the thing I was troubled
about earlier...

Doctor: Yes... Recently, it seems that nurses have
been quitting one after another, making the shift
schedule difficult...

Doctor: Of course, everyone is working hard with
all their heart and soul for the sake of the
patients, but if we had a little more flexibility
in our shift schedule...
Doctor, could you let me help?

Doctor: Eh!? I appreciate your feelings, but it's
quite difficult without any experience...

Actually, I used to work part-time as a nursing
assistant in the past.

I have experience in handling administrative tasks
in other industries as well, so I believe I can be
of help.

Doctor: Hmm... If you could do it, it would be a
great help...

Doctor: ...Understood! I will inform the head
nurse and please let the receptionist know the day
you can come!
Doctor: I'm sorry, but please take care of me.
Yes, please leave it to me.

Doctor: We're short-staffed, so having someone who
can contribute immediately would be a great help.
Please do your best, as much as you can.

Reception Nurse: Ah... I'm feeling horny... I wish
a handsome guy would come in for
hospitalization...
Nurse: The doctor's room is in the back left.

The elderly person who attends diligently says,
There were no abnormalities in the examinations of
yesterday and the day before yesterday, but I
wonder if today is alright...

Elderly woman who can tell the difference: When
you get to be my age, you can tell just by
drinking whether it's generic or not.

Receptionist: The teacher is in the room on the
left.

Receptionist: You must be Ayako Nagatsuki, the new
employee. Please go upstairs and listen to
instructions from each department.
